Here is my extended plan/sketch of the items for the LOI:

In my opinion, BIDS is uniquely positioned that it strives to make data
accessible to both humans (HI) and machines (AI or not), hence I think
its ecosystem is a great match for the call.  And whatever improvements
we had already made recently (schema, validation, bids-examples) benefit
all Is already tremendously!  Even though AI can deduce various
aspects "automatically" AI particularly benefits from clear(er)
structure (data or operationalization) to work with.  

Therefore I am planing to propose a LOI for BIDS which would
expand on that and already ongoing plans for  

- making standard more consistent and better structured (further
  BIDS-study & BIDS 2.0) thus making it easier to not only process
  by HI and AI, but also easier to adopt to other disciplines.

  That would simplify introducing BIDS to, or into BIDS, support for
  other modalities such as various *omics (we might even aim for
  this); as the call actually seems to roll around bio* sciences
  more than neuro*

  - e.g. we are slowing arriving at consensus in
    BEP 036: Phenotypic Data Guidelines
    which would also be example of staying withing "BIDS formalization"

  - potentially establish BIDS forming 'Data Structure Standard'
    https://github.com/bids-standard/bids-2-devel/issues/66

  - ongoing work of Yahya on BEP044: Stimuli and BEP047: audio/video
    recordings to behavioral experiments already finding surprised
    to discover BIDS new potential users  in other fields.


- improving tooling for validation (bids-validator, python
  bids-validator) to ensure valid data (produced by HI, or existing
  converters, and simply critical for AI-driven pipelines). There,
  better integration with validation against other standards (as e.g.
  bids-validator already does for HED and then in dandi-cli we take all
  of those + nwb inspector + zarr + some extra and standardize
  validation records, see https://github.com/con/validation/issues/1 for
  more refs)

- improving observability of the state of the BIDS dataset and study
  overall.  This is CRITICAL for any AI-driven work since humans need to
  be in the loop to introspect what AI had done etc.  Here we have
  chance to work out formalization model within BIDS which different
  "Views" (brainlife, nipoppy, "my"
  https://github.com/OpenNeuroStudies/OpenNeuroStudies etc) could use
  for their custom, potentially wider than BIDS-only, dashboards could
  use

- improving tooling for query & manipulation (pybids, bids-utils),
  exposing them through typical in that stage of AI development (MCP or
  just skills) ways.

  Re bids-utils -- ATM there is NO central library, no upgrade
  mechanisms etc.  Will be critical for HI and AI alike.
  
  - here also, better integration with tools from those other
    'standards' to enrich BIDS datasets for AI use, e.g. AI-driven HED
    annotators, SLEAP estimations for motion etc

- further extending and improving adoption of bids-apps 2.0 and
  boutique descriptor interfaces (Niwrap, Styx) which is critical for
  the net step:

- improving standardization and tooling for carrying out typical
  analytics (bids-models, fitlins) so that also AI-driven frameworks
  (like KOSMOS, etc) and simpler SKILLs could encompass necessary
  analytics in a well formed structured form.

  - here would also fall square into AI-driven BIDS nipreps pipelines
    Oscar I believe had been working on

- with all of the existing and afore-mentioned enhanced goodness improve
  existing AI assistance framework OSA Yahya has developed with BIDS
  support in it, which would then enable HI and AI to operate with
  better focused on BIDS awareness.

- funds for yearly meetup/hackathons so we could all get together and
  process BIDS for HI and AI alike.

So, overall there will be no per se much if any development of neither
AI agentic systems, nor specific datasets; but concentration on
improving BIDS ecosystem (standard, software, AI harnesses) to support
HI and AI, while working toward extending support to other bio* relevant
domains.  So I think this would at large fit also into the large
scopes you identified Franco.

I am open for other ideas/aspects to bring in here!

